# AhaDiff

Use this skill when a coding change should be learned back by the developer.

## Commands

- `ahadiff learn HEAD~1..HEAD` captures the latest commit and generates learning artifacts.
- `ahadiff learn --staged` captures staged changes.
- `ahadiff quiz <run_id>` reviews generated quiz questions.
- `ahadiff review` opens the due SRS queue.
- `ahadiff verify <run_id>` rechecks a run.
- `ahadiff improve <run_id>` runs a targeted improvement loop.
- `ahadiff serve` opens the local WebUI for run inspection.

## Boundaries

- Keep provider credentials in environment variables.
- Do not commit `.ahadiff/audit.private.jsonl`.
- Treat `.ahadiff/review.sqlite`, `.ahadiff/runs/`, and `prompts/` as local
  AhaDiff state unless the repository policy explicitly says otherwise.
- Prefer verified claims with file-line evidence over free-form summaries.
